<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="875" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Fish, Bert/174: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-10T18:00:00-04:00">August 10, 1939—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>45. Department’s 42, July 21, 4 p.m. Your nomination as Minister to
                                Saudi Arabia confirmed August 3. Commission, bearing date August 7,
                                will go forward in near future. You may take oath at any time after
                                receipt this telegram. Instructions and credentials will follow.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>